---

Exercise: how to create a google map

1) Visit the google map example at Google Ajax playground:
https://code.google.com/apis/ajax/playground/#map_simple_v3

2) Copy the source: In the HTML pane, there's a button: "Edit HTML" which will allow you to see the source code.
Click on "Edit HTML". Copy all the source code

3) Paste in a new jsbin HTML page.
---

Encore: Try the same with a polyline example:
https://code.google.com/apis/ajax/playground/#polyline_simple
https://code.google.com/apis/ajax/playground/#polylines_v3

You'll notice all those Geolocation positions: google.maps.LatLng(37.4419, -122.1419),

Bonus: Try to find out the Geolocation of your high school.
Hint: Check out this example

https://code.google.com/apis/ajax/playground/#geocoding_simple
